b"[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe48488.htm)  [Next](sbe48490.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n42\\. A minor one, thus some; (and hence they hold) the existence (of\nexpiation), as in the case of eating. This has been explained.\n\nSome teachers are of opinion that even on the part of Naish _th_ ikas and the\nrest the lapse from chastity constitutes only a minor offence which can be\natoned for by expiatory observances; in the same way as in the case of the\neating of forbidden food the same praya _sk_ itta may be used by the ordinary\nBrahma _k_ arin and by Naish _th_ ikas and the rest. This has been stated by\nthe Sm _ri_ ti writer, 'For the others also (i.e. the Naish _th_ ikas and so\non) the same (rules and\n\np. 707\n\npractices as those for the Upakurvana) hold good, in so far as not opposed to\ntheir a _s_ rama.'\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: 43. But in either case such men stand outside...](sbe48490.htm)\n\n"